Name: dpkg-shlibdeps
URL: https://salsa.debian.org/dpkg-team/dpkg.git
Version: a0828e04289639f875cb924f8d1a65a634683b19
Update Mechanism: Manual
License: GPL-2.0
License File: LICENSE
Security Critical: no
Shipped: no

Description:
Generate shared library substvar dependencies. Chromium vendors
`dpkg-shlibdeps.pl`, the minimal `Dpkg::*` module subset it needs, and the
matching `data/` tables so Linux packaging does not depend on the host
`libdpkg-perl` installation. Chromium also relies on a local
`--ignore-weak-undefined` option. This directory can be removed if that
option becomes available on the buildbots.

Updating:
Copy `dpkg/COPYING` to `third_party/dpkg-shlibdeps/LICENSE`. Then copy
`dpkg/scripts/dpkg-shlibdeps.pl`, the required `dpkg/scripts/Dpkg/*.pm`
dependency closure, and the required `dpkg/data/` files into
`third_party/dpkg-shlibdeps/`.

Patches:
- 0001-dkpg-shlibdeps-add-option-to-ignore-weak-undefined-symbols.patch
  Prevents weak undefined symbols from introducing hard dependencies. Upstream
  merge request:
  https://salsa.debian.org/thomasanderson-guest/dpkg/-/merge_requests/1
